wikipedia_page.main: Percy Smith (born 30 March 1804 in Chichester, Sussex; died 21 February 1876 in Pattiswick, Essex) was an English clergyman and first-class cricketer associated with Cambridge University, active in the 1820s. He is recorded in two matches in 1825, totalling 9 runs with a highest score of 9, holding one catch and taking 2 wickets.
